# =============================================================================
# .gitignore
#
# This repository ships CODE, not measurements. Nothing generated by running
# the code belongs in it: no runs, no scoring JSONs, no figures, no engines,
# no clips. Everything below is either a build product or an output of the
# harness/analysis, and the rules exist so none of it is committed by reflex.
# =============================================================================

# --- Models: never. 6.4 GB, third-party weights, and engines that are wrong on
# --- any machine but the one that built them (see docs/usage/02-models-and-engines.md).
*.onnx
*.pt
*.engine
# The export scratch tree (a torch venv + a DeepStream-Yolo clone + the .pt
# checkpoints) that fetch_models.sh builds — ~5.7 GB of the 6.4.
models/_build/
models/nvdsinfer_custom_impl_Yolo/
models/labels.txt

# --- Compiled objects and libraries -----------------------------------------
*.o
*.d
*.a
*.so
*.so.*
build/
app/build/

# --- Built binaries. These are aarch64 ELFs linked against a specific
# --- DeepStream install; they are reproducible in one `make` and portable to
# --- nothing. Build them, do not commit them.
app/vista_multicam
vista/examples/minimal_pipeline/minimal_pipeline

# --- Video: no clip ships. The office footage shows an identifiable person and
# --- the skew clips are composited from DeepStream sample streams under
# --- NVIDIA's EULA (regenerate with scripts/make_skew_clips.py).
*.mp4
*.mov
*.avi
*.mkv
*.h264

# --- Runs. VISTA_RESULTS defaults here (harness/vista_env.sh), so a campaign
# --- writes here; $VISTA_DATA_ROOT is what you then point the analysis at.
# --- Runs are measurements: they are the thing this repository deliberately
# --- does not distribute.
/runs/

# --- Generated figures and tables. figures/generated/ is where BOTH
# --- figures/src/*.py and analysis/*.py write (FIG_DIR / FIG_OUT, overridable
# --- with $VISTA_FIG_DIR): .tex table fragments and .pdf/.png figures, all of
# --- them derived from run data by code that is already in this tree.
figures/generated/

# --- Scored analysis JSONs, if a data root is put inside the repo. They
# --- normally land in $VISTA_DATA_ROOT/derived, i.e. outside it.
/derived/

# --- Python ------------------------------------------------------------------
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
.venv/
venv/
*.egg-info/

# --- Editors / OS ------------------------------------------------------------
.claude/
.vscode/
.idea/
.DS_Store
*.swp
*~

KNOWN-ISSUES.md